                    <h2 class="font_2" style="font-size:30px; line-height:normal;"><span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family:open sans;"><span style="font-weight:normal;"><span style="font-style:normal;"><span><span style="color:rgb(12, 60, 96);"><span style="letter-spacing:0em;"><span style="font-family:wfont_653b1d_6e9481a128014bf3be167a007dc886ac,wf_6e9481a128014bf3be167a007,orig_hero_new_extrabold;"><span style="color:#000000;"><span style="letter-spacing:normal;"><span style="font-size:30px;">When transferring personal data from the EU</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></h2>

                    <p class="font_8" style="font-size:25px; line-height:normal;"><span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family:open sans;"><span style="font-weight:normal;"><span style="font-style:normal;"><span><span style="color:rgb(12, 60, 96);"><span style="letter-spacing:0em;"><span style="font-family:wfont_454bc7_528f45cef3c34834b4bba54bd4c25952,wf_528f45cef3c34834b4bba54bd,orig_hero_new_regular;"><span style="color:#000000;"><span style="letter-spacing:normal;"><span style="font-size:25px;">The GDPR requires that any data transferred out of the EU must be treated with the same level of protection that the EU privacy laws grant. The privacy laws of the United States generally do not meet that requirement. That is why since GDPR went into effect, Cartingly has offered a data processing addendum and voluntarily participated in the EU-US Privacy Shield Framework as well as the Swiss-US Privacy Shield Framework.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

                    <p class="font_8" style="font-size:25px; line-height:normal;"><span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family:open sans;"><span style="font-weight:normal;"><span style="font-style:normal;"><span><span style="color:rgb(12, 60, 96);"><span style="letter-spacing:0em;"><span style="font-family:wfont_454bc7_528f45cef3c34834b4bba54bd4c25952,wf_528f45cef3c34834b4bba54bd,orig_hero_new_regular;"><span style="color:#000000;"><span style="letter-spacing:normal;"><span style="font-size:25px;">We have incorporated a Data Processing Addendum to our&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration:underline;"><a href="https://igor98052.wixsite.com/website-28" target="_self">Terms of Service</a></span>&nbsp;that is in effect when the GDPR applies to your use of Cartingly Services to process Customer Data as defined in the DPA. You can find the DPA linked within clause 7 of the Uptime, Security and Privacy section. The DPA includes the European Commission’s Standard Contractual Clauses (both controller-processor and controller-controller) to extend GDPR privacy principles, rights, and obligations everywhere personal data is processed. The DPA is extensive so to aid our customers, we have provided both a summary of what they mean and how Yellow upholds our responsibilities in our&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration:underline;"><a href="https://igor98052.wixsite.com/website-28" target="_self">Privacy Regulation Reference</a></span>.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

                    <p class="font_8" style="font-size:25px; line-height:normal;"><span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family:open sans;"><span style="font-weight:normal;"><span style="font-style:normal;"><span><span style="color:rgb(12, 60, 96);"><span style="letter-spacing:0em;"><span style="font-family:wfont_454bc7_528f45cef3c34834b4bba54bd4c25952,wf_528f45cef3c34834b4bba54bd,orig_hero_new_regular;"><span style="color:#000000;"><span style="letter-spacing:normal;"><span style="font-size:25px;">There are also a few ad-hoc cases where EU personal data may be transferred to the US related to Cartingly operations. For instance, if someone in the US comments on our company blog or a customer participates in one of our infrequent surveys or someone applies to one of our open positions or buys swag on our company shop. Such transfers are only occasional and transferred under the&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration:underline;"><a href="https://gdpr-info.eu/art-49-gdpr/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Article 49(1)(b) derogation</a></span>&nbsp;under GDPR.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

